                            <comment id="13219335" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 29 Feb 2012 16:35:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching trivial but actually only against CQL3. It does affect CQL2 too, but in a way, changing the error message could break clients code (if they weren&apos;t very careful) so I figured, why not leaving it the way it is for CQL2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
